  "prompt": "I got a IELTS 6 band on my first attempt. What I should do now?",
  "response": "If you've scored a 6 band on your first IELTS attempt, here are some strategic steps to improve:\n\n1. Understand Your Current Level\n- Analyze your score in each section (Listening, Reading, Writing, Speaking)\n- Identify your weak areas\n\n2. Set a Target Score\n- Determine the score required for your specific goals (university, immigration, etc.)\n- Create a realistic improvement plan\n\n3. Improve Language Skills\n- Practice daily English reading, writing, listening, and speaking\n- Watch English movies, news, podcasts\n- Read English newspapers and books\n- Use language learning apps\n\n4. Targeted Preparation\n- Take IELTS preparation courses\n- Use official IELTS practice materials\n- Solve previous years' question papers\n- Take mock tests to track progress\n\n5. Focus on Weak Areas\n- Writing: Practice essay structures, time management\n- Speaking: Work on fluency, pronunciation\n- Listening: Practice various accents\n- Reading: Improve speed and comprehension\n\n6. Consider Professional Coaching\n- Enroll in IELTS coaching classes\n- Get personalized feedback from experts\n\n7. Take the Test Again\n- Register for the next available test\n- Apply learned strategies\n- Stay confident and calm\n\nRemember, consistent practice is key to improvement.",
